Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: whl.setup
Version: 0.2
Summary: a pip based replacement for ez_setup and setup_requires
Home-page: https://github.com/RonnyPfannschmidt/whl_setup
Author: Ronny Pfannschmidt
Author-email: opensource+whl.setup@ronnypfannschmidt.de
License: UNKNOWN
Description: whl_setup
        ===========
        
        
        an experiment to replace ez_setup and setup_requires with something that works
        the provided mechanism adds a python path where very recent seupptools and setuptools extensions can be installed
        
        installation::
        
            pip install -U whl_setup
            whl_setup_script_install
        
        
        usage::
        
            # setup.py
        
            from whl_setup import setup, Lazy
        
            @Lazy
            def extensions():
                from setuptools import Extension
                return [...]
        
            if __name__ = '__main__':
                setup(
                    ...
                    use_scm_version=True,
                    setup_requires=[
                        'setuptools',
                        'setuptools_scm'
                    ]
                    extensions=extensions,
                    ...
                )
        
Platform: UNKNOWN
